  "text": "[27] The model includes the main species in tropospheric photochemistry, 85 in total, in 161 reactions. Gas phase H 2 SO 4 is produced from the oxidation of SO 2 by the OH radical (K = 8.9 Â 10 À13 cm 3 molecule À1 s À1 [CITATION_1] ). Since the day in question was under a clear sky, no aqueous phase SO 2 oxidation reactions were included. Both condensation and dry deposition are loss processes for H 2 SO 4 . In this case dry deposition, set at 0.5 cm s",
